list.item:
in the hamlet Śrī-Gohālī,
The place name Śrī-Gohālī can also be found in a A fragment of a second plate from Baigram and in A grant of land to monasteries at Śiṣīpuñja, Madhyamasṛgālikā and Grāmakūṭagohālī.
one droṇavāpa of inhabitable terrain;

div.p:
In the case of the village boundaries, those who make their living by farming outside it, cowherds, bord catchers, hunters and others who inhabit the forest should delineate the boundary which is marked by such things as pots–of chaff, charcoal or crockery–shrines, trees, and by familiar markers such as ant hills, 
mounds, depressions, elevations, etc., and paddies, groves, roads, or old dikes. (edition and translqtion 


